<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PaLTM1.2.21">
<l>curuppār kuḻali yacōtai muṉcoṉṉa</l>
<l>tiruppāta kēcattait teṉputu vaippaṭṭaṉ</l>
<l>viruppā luraitta virupatō ṭoṉṟu</l>
<l>muraippārpōy vaikuntat toṉṟuvar tāmē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who say [these] twenty-one [verses] that were spoken with love</l>
<l>by the scholar of southern Puttuvai about [his] sacred head to feet</l>
<l>that had been previously spoken [by] Yaśodā, she with curling hair full of bees,</l>
<l>they will go and unite in Vaikunta.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
